    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing 40 to 100 species of flowering plants, depending upon the classification. Most are tall, often annual, and native to tropical and subtropical regions throughout the world.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
